    {
        "id":"brightport_loudmouth1",
        "message":"I once heard a story about a guy who visited a kingdom ruled by rats--they call it the Ratdom! Haha! People say he disappeared as a child and reappeared a decade later, wearing clothes made entirely of ratskin. He even spoke Rattish! Imagine that, speaking Rattish! Hic. speaking of rats....\n",
        "switchToNPC":"brightportthieves",
        "replies":[
            {
                "text":"N",
                "nextPhraseID":"brightport_loudmouth2"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id":"brightport_loudmouth2",
        "message":"Those folks from Brimhaven--I'd refrain from rudely calling them... hmm, maybe mice. But if anyone resembles a mouse, it would be them. We got a job offer from.. Hic. I\u2019m professional enough not to reveal our clients! Long story short, we ended up declining due to a failure in negotiations. The client then went and hired some local, incompetent bunglers to handle the delicate job! Should\u2019ve seen it coming, considering we wouldn\u2019t budge on the price. Speaking of price...",
        "switchToNPC":"brightportthieves",
        "replies":[
            {
                "text":"Interesting, but i must go now.",
                "nextPhraseID":"X"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id":"brightport_loudmouth3",
        "message":"Speaking of \"Never end\" I was assigned to a job a while ago, up in the north. On my way there, I encountered a small critter. Eager for some fresh meat, I slew it, but what came next was, quite literally, never-ending! A whole group of large beasts were watching me, getting ready to skin my hunt. Once I was distracted enough, they came pouring out of the bushes. I could maybe count a hundred before I went running! I left the meat behind--and even dropped my heirloom skinning knife. Speaking of knives...",
        "switchToNPC":"brightportthieves",
        "replies":[
            {
                "text":"Interesting, but i must go now.",
                "nextPhraseID":"X"
            }
